 GCC 10 AltiVec Vector Keyword Fix
 =================================

 In C++ mode with GCC 10, 'vector' as a type keyword conflicts with std::vector.
 The AltiVec-style 'vector unsigned char' must use '__vector' instead.

 Error message:
   error: ISO C++ forbids declaration of 'type name' with no type

 The fix: Replace 'const vector unsigned char' with 'const __vector unsigned char'

 Apply with:
 -----------

 python3 -c "
 content = open('Lexer.cpp').read()
 content = content.replace('const vector unsigned char', 'const __vector unsigned char')
 open('Lexer.cpp', 'w').write(content)
 print('Fixed AltiVec vector keyword')
 "

 Or with sed:
 ------------

 sed -i 's/const vector unsigned char/const __vector unsigned char/g' Lexer.cpp

 Location in file (around line 3270):
 ------------------------------------

 BEFORE:
   const vector unsigned char *Ptr = reinterpret_cast<const vector unsigned char*>(Start);

 AFTER:
   const __vector unsigned char *Ptr = reinterpret_cast<const __vector unsigned char*>(Start);
